<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10125e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10125e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10125e"> 125(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> made large demands</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Drama League Pirandello&apos;s Henry IV. Provided the audience at the Abbey Theatre on the 27th and 28th ult. with a brilliant, if mystifying play, and, more interesting still, revealed to them in Mr. Paul Ruttledge an actor of genius. Perhaps to the hardened playgoer Mr. Ruttledge&apos;s extraordinary intensity in the part of &ldquo;Henry IV.&rdquo; would not have been so astonishing <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The part was one that <mark>made large demands</mark> on the actor. <small> <a name="IS3may24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IS3may24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (3 May 1924) 242/2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
